Subject: Re: [T2] heating a bus

FIX THAT GAS HEATER!!  A gas heater is the BEST way to heat a bus, but  you
need to rebuild your heater, change the fuel lines and put a new exhaust on
it.  If you need rebuild parts, go to:

http://pages.prodigy.net/busbarn/southwind.html


For those of you at the RMMW show this past summer, maybe you heard the
quiet "roar" of the gas heaters coming on and off in the Colorado busses
all night.  Those people who camp in the cold have figured out a good
working gas heater is a VERY nice addition on those cold nights.


>i have a 71 non pop top camper that i need to heat... i can not use stock
>heat exchanges due to a cheezy aftermarket header(soon to be replace)
>i have an old stewart warner gas heater already mounted int the bus but it
>smokes, i don't trust it while driving with my two children breathing in the
>back... is it worth working on the gas heater.. it seems to pump out the
>BTUs and heats the bus wonderfully but it also turns the bus into a gas
>chamber.. would i be better off going with propane?
